                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#2r">f. 2r</locus>
                           <desc>: Note on the number of books in the monastic library followed by a
                              hymn praising the Virgin Mary.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> 37 books were in the library of the monastery at the time when the
                              note was written. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#182va">f. 182va</locus>
                           <desc>: Rhymed ownership note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#182va">182va</locus>: ዝንቱ፡ ወንጌል፡ ዘጽርሐ፡ ቅድሳት፤ ከመ፡
                              ይዝክርዋ፡ በጊዜ፡ ጸሎት፡ አማኅፀንኩክሙ፡ ትቤ፡ ለማኅበር፡ ዘደብረ፡ ገነት፡ ወለወልዳ፡ ተርቢኖስ። ወለአቡሃ፡
                              ዘመለኮት፡ ወለእማ፡ አርአያ፡ ኅሪት፨</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#182va">182va</locus>: This Gospel (book belongs) to
                              the chamber of sacred things. That they remember it in the time of
                              prayer, I supplicate you; you say to the community of Dabra Gannat,
                              and its son Tärbinos, and its father Za-Mäläkot, and its mother
                              ʾArʾaya Ḫǝrit (?).</quote>
                           <note> Written in the main hand. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#182vb">ff. 182vb-183</locus>
                           <desc>ra: Extensive note, for the most part erased.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/> The greater part of the text (<locus target="#182vb">182vb</locus>
                           <note>) has been erased, although some letters are still visible. The
                              legible paqssage contains the condemnation formula. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#183ra">f. 183ra</locus>
                           <desc>-rb: Donation note concerning land.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#183ra">183ra-</locus>rb: ዘወሀበት፡ ሐመልማለ፡ ወርቅ፡ ገራኅተ፡ ፃዕዳ፡
                              ሐመድ፡ ለአበ፡ ነፍሳ፡ ቄስ፡ ወልደ፡ ክርስቶስ፡&lt;...&gt; ተዝካራሂ፡ ግበሩ፡ አመ፡ ፴ሁ፡ ለጥቅምት፡
                              በጊዜ፡ ቊርባን፡ ኢትርሥዑ፡ ስማ፡ ለዓለም።</quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in the main hand, the beginning is missing. About half of
                              the text has been erased. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus target="#183rb">f. 183rb</locus>
                           <desc>: Note on commomoration days of some individuals. </desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in the main hand. The note lists the dates on which the
                              deceased ʾAkalä Krǝstos, Walda Krǝstos, Giyorgis and Ṗāwlos are
                              commemorated. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a6">
                           <locus target="#183v">f. 183v</locus>
                           <desc>: Short note on the Gospels and Evangelists. </desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in the main hand. The final part is unintelligible.
                           </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Crude notes: <locus target="#1r">1r</locus>.
 -
                           Crude note in the upper margin: <locus target="#3r">3r</locus>.
 -
                           Numerous glosses or corrections written in a different hand, throughout
                           the Ms.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- White threads are inserted in the upper corner of
                              some folios. - Titles of the chapters are written in the upper
                              margin.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
